case.comments: 美国第一例新肺炎患者，机器人配备摄像头、麦克风和听诊器，主治医生隔着玻璃窗户，操作医疗机器人进行治疗。患者住院前6天没有好转，第七天服用了一种治疗埃博拉病毒的实验性药物Remdesivir。之后迅速治愈，目前已经出院。
case.comments_en: The man, in his 30s, was the first confirmed case of US. He was evaluated using a robot. Fully recovered by now.

case.comments: 丈夫没有去过武汉，被间接感染，成为美国Person to person传染的第一例。
case.comments_en: A Chicago woman in her 60s returned to the United States on Jan. 13 from Wuhan, China. She's in stable condition and doing well.

case.comments: 这位患者的信息很少。入境机场和入境时间均无报道提及。
case.comments_en: A man in his fifties who arrived from Wuhan at LAX — is currently in isolation in a local hospital and in good condition.

case.comments: 亚利桑那州立大学学生。去过疫情爆发地 - 华南海鲜市场。并未住校内宿舍，而是在Tempe租房。
case.comments_en: ASU student who visited Wuhan recently. He lives in Tempe, not on campus.

case.comments: 患者到达洛杉矶机场之后，从机场立刻被送往医院。
case.comments_en: The patient arrived in Los Angeles Airport and was immediately sent to hospital.

case.comments: 美国第二例、芝加哥第一例确诊者的丈夫。没有去过疫区，是美国首例人传人。他在PIRHL LLC工作，曾去俄亥俄cleveland办公室出差。其孙子已经有发烧症状【已排除】
case.comments_en: First person-to-person transmission case. Husband of Chicago's first confirmed case. Works for PIRHL LLC. Recently visited the company's Cleveland office.

case.comments: 除两次出门看病外，没有离开家。
case.comments_en: First Bay Area Case. He recently traveled to Wuhan. He has largely been isolated at home since he returned to San Jose International Airport on Jan. 24 and only left his home twice to seek outpatient medical care.

case.comments: Umass Boston学生，二十多岁。
case.comments_en: UMass Boston student, young man in 20s

case.comments: 这对夫妇，丈夫从中国返回，就没离开家。【update】夫妻病情恶化后，被转移到UCSF治疗，但患者于3/4号痊愈。
case.comments_en:
The San Benito County cases are a husband and wife, both 57. The husband recently traveled to Wuhan, but his wife did not travel with him.

Both San Benito County coronavirus patients recovered

case.comments: 没去过武汉，被丈夫传染。【update】夫妻病情恶化后，被转移到UCSF治疗，但患者于3/4号痊愈。
case.comments_en:
Person to person transmission, by her husband.

Both San Benito County coronavirus patients recovered

case.comments: 除两次出门看病，没有离开家。
case.comments_en: A female who traveled from China to visit family in Santa Clara County is the second Bay Area case.Since arriving on January 23, she has only left her family's home twice to seek outpatient medical care

case.comments: 美国第十二例，威斯康星第一例确诊。所在地是madison，威斯康星大学主校区。患者过去两周去过中国，在国内接触过的人里有人确诊。这位患者目前情况良好，不需要住院，已经回家隔离。威斯康星还有十人在被检测，七人已经被排除(test negative)。出于隐私保护，患者所有信息保密。
case.comments_en: The patient is a Wisconsin resident who recently visited Beijing, China. the patient is doing well and is no longer in the hospital.

case.comments: 患者之前随撤侨飞机从武汉返美，在圣地亚哥一个美军基地入境。美国CDC对随机返回者进行隔离两周。患者目前状况良好，正在被继续隔离。评论：两次撤侨目前仅发现一人确诊，比例之低，美国真是开挂！
case.comments_en: The patient had been evacuated from Wuhan and under a 14-day quarantine at Marine Corps Air Station Miramar. Minimal symptoms. The patient had initially been released  back to quarantine after a possible mix-up with the test results.

case.comments: 美国确诊第十四例，也是之前撤侨飞机上回来的，2月7日入境之后在圣地亚哥一个美军基地被隔离。
case.comments_en: The patient returned to the U.S. on a State Department-chartered flight. Under a federal quarantine order after arrival on Feb 7, 2020.

case.comments: 美国第十五例确诊：2月7日从武汉返美的撤侨人员，性别男。一直在圣安东尼奥一处美军基地。同行91人都在被继续隔离。
case.comments_en: The individual was part of a group that arrived at San Antonio Air Force base on a State Department-chartered flight from Wuhan. Of the 91 people on the flight, only one showed symptoms.

case.comments: 日本游轮钻石公主号撤侨返回人员。目前在Napa。这是湾区第五例。
case.comments_en: First case in Napa County. Among the dozens of Americans on the Princess Diamond cruise ship under quarantine in Japan.

case.comments: 美国第17例，患者在加州一个偏远的地方。目前健康状况良好，在家隔离。官方没有透露其他任何消息。
case.comments_en: First case of COVID-19 confirmed in Humboldt County. Doing well and self-isolating at home

case.comments: 加州首府Sacramento确诊该郡第一例患者。患者返美旅途中就采取了防范措施，回到加州后自我隔离，目前情况良好，在家继续隔离。
case.comments_en: 1st case of coronavirus in Sacramento County. Doing quite well.

case.comments: 德州圣安东尼奥美军基地新增两例确诊，患者均为钻石公主号撤侨人员。
case.comments_en: Two evacuees from the Diamond Princess who were quarantined at Joint Base San Antonio-Lackland are infected with coronavirus.

case.comments: 之前，日本游轮钻石公主号撤侨人员里有3例确诊。2月21日，CDC宣布，累计有18人确诊，但没有提供细节。
case.comments_en: 18 total cases among returnees from Diamond Princess. No further details.

case.comments: 日本游轮钻石公主号撤侨人员再确诊18人，美国共计53例。
case.comments_en: Another 18 cases confirmed among returnees from Diamond Princess.

case.comments: 美国累计确诊57例，其中40例是日本钻石公主号游轮撤侨人员。
case.comments_en: US total cases reached 57. 40 from Diamond Princess cruise returnees.

case.comments: 钻石公主号游轮撤侨人员累计确诊42例，武汉撤侨人员确诊累计3例。
case.comments_en: So far, 42 total cases confirmed from Diamond Princess cruise returnees. 3 cases from Wuhan Chartered-flight returnees.

case.comments: 美国确诊首例不明传染途径病例，患者在北加，近期没有离开美国，也没有接触过确诊患者。这也是美国的第60例。
case.comments_en: 1st U.S. Coronavirus Case Of Unknown Origin From Solano County.

case.comments: 从日本游轮上下来，转到Marin hospital 医院进行治疗，这位患者是一位没有症状患者。
case.comments_en: Confirmed the transfer of one patient with laboratory-confirmed novel coronavirus (COVID-19) from Travis Air Force Base in Solano County to a Marin County hospital. An asymptomatic patient -- meaning the patient does not show symptoms of the virus, such as fever or difficulty breathing -- was transported to a Marin hospital on Wednesday night. The patient who tested positive for COVID-19 is one of the evacuees from the quarantined Diamond Princess cruise ship in Japan.

case.comments: 钻石公主号游轮撤侨人员再确诊两例，共计44例。
case.comments_en: 2 more cases confirmed from Diamond Princess returnees. total cruise ship returnee cases reached 44.

case.comments: 美国第63例确诊患者、湾区/北加第二例不明传染源患者，65岁的女性，没有去过疫区，没有跟确诊患者接触过。【更新】该患者于3/9病逝。
case.comments_en: 2nd U.S. Coronavirus Case Of Unknown Origin Discovered In Santa Clara County. 65 years old female. [Update] She passed away on Mar 9th.

case.comments: 这位患者在一所小学工作。2月19日开始有症状，俄勒冈Hillsboro一个实验室使用了CDC提供的检测工具，目前在等CDC正式确认，但既然州里发布了新闻，并且关闭了他任职的学校进行消毒，相信是test positive（确诊）。此人没有去过疫区、没有跟确认患者接触过，传染源不明（也就是community-transmitted）。
case.comments_en: A Lake Oswego elementary school employee contracted Oregon’s first case, causing the closure of the 430-student school.

case.comments: 男中学生，Jackson High School in Mill Creek，未知传染源，周一身体不适，感觉好点之后继续回校，周五确诊。目前在家隔离。
case.comments_en:
Student at Jackson High School announced Friday, isolating at home.

A Student at Jackson High School in Mill Creek (Everett Public Schools). Unknown Origin.

case.comments: King County 50来岁的女性，USPS员工，去过韩国，2月23返美工作。目前在家隔离，但无大碍。周二感觉不适，周三自动汇报，也是周五确诊。USPS发言人表示，患者在西雅图Federal Way分发中心工作，是一个信件处理工厂，以散件形式分发USPS营销信件和包裹服务。该厂不处理纸质信件，也不投递信件。
case.comments_en: A woman in her 50s who had traveled to South Korea. She turned to be the confirmed USPS Federal Way employee. Her work site is a network distribution center that doesn't deliver mails directly.

case.comments: 华盛顿州长宣布：king county出现美国首例新冠肺炎死亡。目前只知道是位男性（州长声明里使用 his），其他信息不明，下午1点会有新闻发布会。昨天全美确诊66例，第66例恰好也在华盛顿州，去过韩国，但是位女性。所以他是第67例。【更新】这名男性曾经住院，病逝于 EvergreenHealth。
case.comments_en: First death caused by coronavirus in U.S. A King County man in his 50s died at EvergreenHealth hospital.

case.comments: 在华盛顿州kirkland一家名为LifeCare的养老院，一位70多位的老妇人病情比较严重，在EvergreenHealth医院接受治疗，于3/2病逝
case.comments_en: A woman in her 70s who was a resident of LifeCare in Kirkland and is hospitalized at EvergreenHealth.

case.comments: 这位女性40来岁，是kirkland养老院LifeCare的工作人员，她周四就被送往Overlake医院了。养老院一共有108位老人和180位工作人员，其中有27位老人和25位工作人员有疑似症状。这位
case.comments_en: A woman in her 40s who employed by LifeCare. She remains hospitalized at Overlake Medical Center. The facility has 108 residents and 180 employees. 27 residents and 25 employees have symptoms.

case.comments: Illinois, Cook County 新增一例，患者正在医院隔离，70多岁男子，情况稳定
case.comments_en: A man in his 70s in suburban Cook County tested positive. The third case in Illinois.

case.comments: 跟Santa Clara2月28周五（未知传染源）确诊的人有过”household“接触。但这位成年女性 not hospitalized or ill
case.comments_en: An adult woman who "is a household contact of the third Santa Clara County case."

case.comments: 患者男性，40来岁，近期去过意大利。回美之后，并没有去公司工作，接触的人有限。评论：有些新闻提到了”in their 40s“和”since their return“，但只说一人确诊，估计是一家人一起去意大利。
case.comments_en: A man in 40s. Traveled to Italy in mid-February. Didn't go back to work after his return. Very limited contact with others.

case.comments: 华盛顿州一位60来岁的男性患者确诊，目前在Valley Medical Center in Renton，这位患者情况不太好：in critical but stable condition
case.comments_en: A man in his 60s. In critical but stable condition at Valley Medical Center in Renton.

case.comments: 华盛顿州一位60来岁的男性患者确诊，目前在Virginia Mason Medical Center. 他的情况危急 in critical condition
case.comments_en: A man in his 60s. In critical condition at Virginia Mason Medical Center

case.comments: 医护感染，在NorthBay VacaValley Hospital工作，接触过之前UC Davis医学中心治疗的社区传播患者，居家隔离中。
case.comments_en: NorthBay VacaValley Hospital health care worker. In isolation at home. Exposed to the community-acquired case hospitalized at UC Davis Medical Center.

case.comments: 医护感染，在NorthBay VacaValley Hospital工作，接触过之前UC Davis医学中心治疗的社区传播患者，居家隔离中。
case.comments_en: NorthBay VacaValley Hospital health care worker. In isolation at home. Exposed to the community-acquired case hospitalized at UC Davis Medical Center.

case.comments: 成年女性，患有慢性疾病，已住院。
case.comments_en: A woman who officials said has chronic health conditions. Hospitalized

case.comments: 成年男性，是另一确诊病例的丈夫，患有慢性疾病，已住院，有埃及旅行史。
case.comments_en: A husband and wife who recently traveled to Egypt. Hospitalized.

case.comments: 成年女性，是另一确诊病例的妻子，已住院，有埃及旅行史。
case.comments_en: A husband and wife who recently traveled to Egypt. Hospitalized.

case.comments: 30多岁女性，住在纽约曼哈顿，去过伊朗，居家隔离中，是Emergency medical services的工作人员， 也是纽约市第一例确诊病例的应急人员。
case.comments_en: First Confirmed Case in New York. A woman in her 30s returned from Iran last week. She is an EMS worker and  is the first NYC emergency responder with a confirmed case.

case.comments: 80多岁女性， EvergreenHealth in Kirkland住院，有基础疾病，情况危重。【更新】3月1日病逝。
case.comments_en: A female in her 80s, hospitalized at EvergreenHealth in Kirkland. The woman has underlying health conditions, and is in critical condition

case.comments: 90多岁女性， EvergreenHealth in Kirkland住院，有基础疾病，情况危重. 【更新】3月3日病逝。
case.comments_en: A female in her 90s, hospitalized at EvergreenHealth in Kirkland. The woman has underlying health conditions, and is in critical condition

case.comments: 70多岁男性，EvergreenHealth in Kirkland住院，有基础疾病，情况危重。
case.comments_en: A male in his 70s, hospitalized at EvergreenHealth in Kirkland. The man has underlying health conditions, and is in critical condition

case.comments: 70多岁男性，EvergreenHealth in Kirkland治疗，有基础疾病，2月29日病逝
case.comments_en: Second coronavirus death in King County. A male in his 70s was hospitalized at EvergreenHealth. He had underlying health conditions and died on 2/29/20

case.comments: 40多岁男性， 在Kirkland的EvergreenHealth住院。他是 Snohomish 县居民。他并不是 LifeCare 的员工。他有基础疾病。病逝。
case.comments_en:
Previously announced male in his 40s hospitalized at EvergreenHealth in Kirkland has died. The patient was a Snohomish County resident. He was not an employee at LifeCare. He did have underlying conditions. No additional details are available at this time. 

Third case in Snohomish County. A male in his 40s, hospitalized at EvergreenHealth in Kirkland. In critical condition.

case.comments: Sarasota市一位60多岁成年人，近期没有去过CDC限制旅行的国家。
case.comments_en: An adult in Manatee County

case.comments: Hillsborough一位成年人，去过意大利。
case.comments_en: An adult in Hillsborough County with a history of travel to Italy.

case.comments: 青少年，去过意大利，轻症，居家隔离中
case.comments_en: 2nd person in RI. A teenage girl took part in a mid-February trip to Europe organized by St. Raphael’s Academy

case.comments: 患者解除隔离后，第二次检测呈阳性，重新隔离中。此案例有疑问是否该算在武汉撤侨中，CDC和TX官网都未收录。
case.comments_en:
CDC mistakenly released a patient from the San Antonio Texas Center for Infection Disease Sunday. The patient returned to isolation after a pending, subsequent lab test came up positive.

Not sure if this one should be Wuhan exvacuee. This case wasn't count in CDC website nor TX official website https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/php/preparing-communities.html

case.comments: 是俄勒冈州第一例患者的家庭接触者，居家隔离中
case.comments_en: 2nd Oregon case, household contact with the first case in Oregon

case.comments: 3月2日早晨，CDC网站汇报钻石公主号游轮撤侨人员中新增一例、累计45例。
case.comments_en: Confirmed case increased by one and reached a total of 45 from Diamond Princess returnees, according to CDC website.

case.comments: 新罕布什尔州首例，去过意大利，在家治疗中
case.comments_en: 1st case in NH, patient had recently traveled to Italy and is now receiving treatment at home.

case.comments: 是伊利诺伊州第3例的妻子，70多岁，在家治疗中，情况稳定
case.comments_en: The individual is a woman in her 70s and is the spouse of the third case – a man in his 70s.  This fourth case is quarantined at home and is complying with health officials.  Both cases are reported to be in good condition.

case.comments: Oregon第3例，曾去过Umatilla County middle school的青少年篮球赛，在Providence St. Mary Medical Center治疗。与Oregon前2例无关，不明途径感染，属社区传播。
case.comments_en: 3rd Oregon case, an adult who attended a youth basketball game at a Umatilla County middle school. The person is now at Providence St. Mary Medical Center. unrelated to the two others in Oregon, and the state is treating it as a “community transmission,”

case.comments: 在其他县与确诊病人接触；目前在家隔离。
case.comments_en: an adult male who had contact with a confirmed case in another county and is now under home isolation.

case.comments: 在Santa Clara县与确诊病人接触；目前在家隔离。
case.comments_en: an adult male who had contact with a previously confirmed case in Santa Clara County. That person is also under home isolation.

case.comments: San Mateo County第2例确诊（San Mateo County首例是撤侨确诊病例转院），成年人。在医院隔离。传染源未知。
case.comments_en: An adult who is currently in isolation at the hospital. The county says the source of that person's exposure is unknown.

case.comments: 80多岁女性，LifeCare养老院居民。在EvergreenHealth 住院，目前情况危重。
case.comments_en: A female in her 80s, a resident of LifeCare, was hospitalized at EvergreenHealth. She is in critical condition.

case.comments: 患者从旧金山到墨西哥到邮轮返回，在 Sonoma 县居住的10天中发现新冠症状。目前已在当地医院隔离。
case.comments_en: The patient had recently returned from a cruise ship that departed from San Francisco to Mexico. The patient, who has been in Sonoma County for 10 days, is showing symptoms of coronavirus and is currently in stable condition and under isolation at a local hospital.

case.comments: 40多岁女性，目前住院，有基础疾病。
case.comments_en: A female in her 40s, currently hospitalized with underlying health conditions.

case.comments: 加州第24例确诊，是与另一位确诊在Solano County的患者有过接触的医护人员
case.comments_en: A resident in Placer County has presumptively tested positive for the Coronavirus Disease 2019, according to the Placer County Public Health.

case.comments: 麻州第2例，二十多岁女性，住在Norfolk County，和学校组团去过意大利，曾随同Rhode Island一所Catholic High School一同去过Italy，且在旅途当中至少同RI州已被确诊的两名患者中的一人有过频繁接触，回来后出现新冠症状，现居家恢复中。
case.comments_en: 2nd case in MA. A woman in her 20s who lives in Norfolk County, had traveled to Italy with a school group and came down with symptoms of the coronavirus. She is recovering at home.

case.comments: 乔治亚首例， 在Fulton County， 男性，去过意大利米兰，现在都在家中隔离。
case.comments_en: 1st in Georgia. Man, had traveled to Milan, Italy. Being quarantined inside their home.

case.comments: 乔治亚第2例， 在Fulton County， 是乔治亚第1例去过意大利米兰的患者家庭接触者。
case.comments_en: 2nd in Georgia, household of the 1st case who traveled to Milan, Italy. Being quarantined inside their home.

case.comments: 70多岁男性，LifeCare养老院居民。在Kirkland 的 EvergreenHealth 住院，有基础疾病。3/1/2020 病逝。
case.comments_en: A male in his 70s, a resident of LifeCare, hospitalized at EvergreenHealth in Kirkland. The man had underlying health conditions, and died 3/1/20

case.comments: 70多岁女性，LifeCare养老院居民。在EvergreenHealth 住院，有基础疾病。3/1/2020 病逝。
case.comments_en: A female in her 70s, a resident of LifeCare, hospitalized at EvergreenHealth in Kirkland. The woman had underlying health conditions, and died 3/1/20

case.comments: 50多岁男性，在 Highline 医院住院。无已知传染源。情况稳定但是病情危重，他先前没有基础疾病。
case.comments_en: A male in his 50s, hospitalized at Highline Hospital. No known exposures. He is in stable but critical condition. He had no underlying health conditions.

case.comments: Sacramento官网3/2最新数据显示，在第一例确诊后，又有两例确诊。
case.comments_en: Two additional cases are confirmed according to the official website (updated on 3/2)

case.comments: 【更新】这例病例现在被很多媒体归为NYC，特此修正。纽约州第2例，住在Westchester，在曼哈顿工作， 没有过直接接触史，但是去过迈阿密。现在在医院治疗。
case.comments_en: This case was counted in NYC. The 2nd in New York, commute worker in Manhanttan. He is now hospitalized with an underlying respiratory illness. No direct connection to China or any country on the watch list. However, he did travel to Miami.

case.comments: 一名20多岁的男子，没有住院，在家治疗中。该男子是一位州外去过社区传播地区的确诊病例的接触者。
case.comments_en: A man in his 20s who is not hospitalized and is recovering at home. The man is a known contact of a "presumptive positive" coronavirus case outside of Arizona who recently traveled to an area with community spread of the virus

case.comments: 佛罗里达州第3例， 病人是之前确诊患者的妹妹。她们都去过意大利。这位确诊患者的室友也正在测试中。
case.comments_en: A third presumptive positive case of COVID-19 coronavirus has been found in Florida. She is the sister of the Hillsborough County woman who tested positive Sunday after a trip to Italy.

case.comments: 第7例死亡病例， 病人也来自LifeCare养老院，于上周被送往Harborview Medical Center并于两天后死亡，死亡六天后被确诊。
case.comments_en: A person who died last week in a Seattle hospital had the coronavirus, tests have shown, , and raising the death toll in the country to seven.

case.comments: 华州，King county新增病例，40多岁女性，系Life Center工作人员，未曾住院，目前在家恢复中。

case.comments: 洛杉矶再确诊2例，其中一例为洛杉矶机场的医疗检察员
case.comments_en: 2 additional cases, including second medical screener at LAX, confirmed in LA.

case.comments: 患者是一位60余岁的男性，目前正在住院治疗。患者的样本在新泽西州卫生局检测出阳性，现已被送往CDC进行最终确认。
case.comments_en: A male in his 60s who is currently hospitalized in stable condition at Jefferson Cherry Hill Hospital. The presumptive positive result came from a sample tested by the New Jersey Department of Health at the New Jersey Public Health Environmental Laboratories (PHEL) and is now being submitted to the CDC for confirmatory testing

case.comments: 华州Jefferson County确诊一例，University of Washington宣布取消线下授课
case.comments_en: One case in Jefferson County confirmed; University of Washington announced that starting on Monday classes will no longer be meeting in person through the end of winter quarter.

case.comments: 三位患者都在2月11至21日搭乘了至尊公主号游轮前往墨西哥。目前三人症状轻微，在家隔离。
case.comments_en: The three new cases were from South and Mid Placer and all traveled on the Grand Princess cruise ship from San Francisco to Mexico Feb. 11-21. Two had mild symptoms that have already resolved; the third currently has mild symptoms. All three are isolated at home and none required hospitalization.

case.comments: 最新消息称King County已有共58例确诊患者
case.comments_en: As of the 11 a.m. Department of Health Update, there were 58 cases in King County, 19 cases in Snohomish County, one case in Grant County and one case in Jefferson County, which includes Port Townsend on the Olympic Peninsula.

case.comments: 最新消息称Snohomish County已有共19例确诊患者
case.comments_en: As of the 11 a.m. Department of Health Update, there were 58 cases in King County, 19 cases in Snohomish County, one case in Grant County and one case in Jefferson County, which includes Port Townsend on the Olympic Peninsula.

case.comments: 明州Ramsay郡的一名老年女性被确认为明州首例。该患者之前曾乘坐游轮，2月25日出现症状，3月3日就诊。现在在家中隔离恢复。
case.comments_en: A Ramsey County woman is the first to have a presumptive case of the new COVID-19 coronavirus in Minnesota. The case is an older woman who recently travelled on a cruise ship and is now recovering at home.The patient began to develop symptoms on Feb. 25 and sought health care on Mar. 3.

case.comments: 肯塔基州确认首例。患者在Lexington，已经隔离。目前没有更详细的信息。
case.comments_en: Gov. Beshear confirmed the case was in Lexington, and the person is isolated. Beshear declared a state of emergency, but said the threat to the general population is low.

case.comments: 两位丹佛市居民被确诊。均表现出症状，但尚未住院。两位患者最近都有州外的旅游史， 一位患者刚从加拿大温哥华回来，另一位患者坐了邮轮回来，但是官方没有给出邮轮的具体信息。这两位患者是科罗拉多州的第4，5位患者。
case.comments_en:
Denver health officials on Friday said two city residents have tested positive for the novel coronavirus.
both patients recently returned from out-of-state travel — one from Vancouver, Canada, and one from a cruise ship, though officials did not say where the cruise had gone.

case.comments: 内布拉斯加州首例，曾去往英国。周四出现严重肺炎症状和细菌感染。目前其家人是否感染仍然未知，与此同时工作人员正在调查与之相关的接触者和地点。
case.comments_en: The first Nebraskan to test positive for the coronavirus is a 36-year-old Omaha woman. It is currently unknown whether the patient's immediate family members have been exposed. An investigation is underway by an epidemiology team to see who else this individual has had contact with and where.

case.comments: 停泊在旧金山附近的Grand Princess游轮目前有46人检测，21确诊，其中2个游客和19船员。
case.comments_en: 21 out of 46 people tested positive for #coronavirus on the cruise ship in San Francisco 2 passengers and 19 crew member.

case.comments: 纽约3月6日下午新增11例中在Westchester的8例。
case.comments_en: 8 of the new new cases are in Westchester County

case.comments: 俄克拉荷马州第一例确诊。50多岁男性，去过意大利，于2/23返回TULSA。现在在家中自我隔离。
case.comments_en: First confirmed case in Oklahoma. The patient is a man in his 50′s who recently traveled to Italy, and then returned to Tulsa on February 23rd. He was not showing symptoms at the time, but did become symptomatic on February 29.

case.comments: 纽约3月6日下午新增11例中在Nassau的3例。
case.comments_en: 3 of the new cases are in Nassau County

case.comments: 40来岁男性，近期去过加州。
case.comments_en: A man in his 40s who recently traveled to California

case.comments: 新泽西第4例确诊，是一位50多岁的男子，目前在卑尔根县的恩格尔伍德医院和医疗中心接受治疗。这名患者自周四以来一直住院治疗。
case.comments_en: 4th Presumptive Positive Case of Coronavirus In NJ, a man in his 50s, is hospitalized at Englewood Hospital and Medical Center in Bergen County. The individual has been hospitalized since Thursday.

case.comments: Santa Clara今日确诊4人-男性，目前隔离在家，与之前确诊患者有接触。
case.comments_en: 4 more cases confirmed in Santa Clara today. Adult male, isolated at home. Household contact of a previously confirmed case in Santa Clara County.

case.comments: Santa Clara今日确诊4人-女性，现在医院治疗，无更多细节。
case.comments_en: 4 more cases confirmed in Santa Clara today. Adult female, currently hospitalized. This case is under investigation.

case.comments: Santa Clara今日确诊4人-男性，现在医院治疗，曾前往印度。
case.comments_en: 4 more cases confirmed in Santa Clara today. Adult male, currently hospitalized. Recently traveled from India.

case.comments: Santa Clara今日确诊4人-男性，现在医院治疗，无更多细节。
case.comments_en: 4 more cases confirmed in Santa Clara today. Adult male, isolated at home. Exposure details are under investigation. ​

case.comments: 南卡罗莱纳州第一例确诊。一位老年女性检测结果阳性，正在医院隔离。
case.comments_en: One patient is an elderly adult female from Kershaw County who has been hospitalized and is in isolation. She has been tested presumptive positive.

case.comments: 南卡罗莱纳州第二例确诊。一位成年女性检测结果阳性，正在家中隔离。近期到访过法国和意大利。
case.comments_en: A second patient is an adult female from Charleston County who recently traveled to France and Italy. The patient did not require hospitalization and is self-isolated at home. She has been tested presumptive positive.

case.comments: 伊利诺伊州第6例确诊，50多岁女性， 在Vaughn Occupational High School工作。这名女子是2月21日下船的至尊公主号游轮上的乘客之一。几天后她回到了芝加哥的家。当这个女人回到芝加哥后，她回到了高中工作，目前正在住院治疗，病情稳定。
case.comments_en: The state’s sixth case of novel coronavirus is a Chicago woman in her 50s employed at Vaughn Occupational High School. An official with the Illinois Department of Health said the woman was one of the people aboard the Grand Princess Cruise Ship that disembarked on Feb. 21. She returned home to Chicago a few days later.

case.comments: 德州新增2例病例，这两名患者是两名60多岁的女性，她们是在前往埃及的旅途中接触到这种病毒的。这些妇女在家中进行自我隔离，其中一人出现轻微症状，另一人不再有症状。
case.comments_en: Two more cases of the new coronavirus have been reported in Fort Bend County, two women in their 60s, were exposed to the virus as part of a trip to Egypt. The women are self-quarantined at home, one with mild symptoms and the other no longer symptomatic.

case.comments: 夏威夷首例确诊，是夏威夷当地居民，曾于二月底在Oahu登上至尊公主号游轮。
case.comments_en: 1st case in Hawaii. The person infected is a Hawaii resident who was a passenger aboard the Grand Princess cruise ship that docked on Oahu in late February.

case.comments: 第3例，60多岁女性，与前两例不同的是她是第一个与最近圣拉斐尔学院海外之行无关的本地病例。但是，她曾经与一位在纽约被确诊的患者有过面对面的接触。她现在在家，症状轻微。这名女子是史密斯菲尔德大道幼儿园（Smithfield Avenue Nursery School）的一名员工。
case.comments_en: Another Rhode Islander, a woman in her 60s, has tested positive for the novel coronavirus, state health officials announced Friday evening, and she is the first local case not tied to a recent St. Raphael Academy trip overseas.

case.comments: CO 第7例和第8例， 两名女性都有过出国旅行。 一名40多岁，一名70多岁。
case.comments_en: The sixth and seventh cases were reported in Highlands Ranch Friday afternoon. Woman in her 40s and Woman in her 70s, exposed during international travel.

case.comments: CO 第八例确诊，50多岁女性， 在Eagle County， 有过出国旅行的经历。
case.comments_en: 8th case in CO, from Eagle County, A Woman in her 50s — exposed during international trave

case.comments: 华州新增1例，也是Pierce County第一例确诊病例。是一名50多岁的男性，身体状况不佳。他在吉伯港的圣安东尼医院接受治疗。
case.comments_en: One new case in WA, this would also be the first case confirmed from Pierce County. A man in his 50s with underlying health conditions. He is at St. Anthony’s Hospital in Gig Harbor receiving treatment.

case.comments: 佛州新增三例中的2例， 在Broward County
case.comments_en: There are three new case in FL, two new cases in Broward County considered to be isolated.

case.comments: 佛州新增三例中的1例，来自Lee County，已经病逝。【更新】该病患享年70余岁。
case.comments_en: There are three new case in FL, the third new case is in Lee County, and that patient has died. [UPDATE] the patient was in his / her seventies.

case.comments: 犹他州首例确诊，一位60岁以上的病人，已经家中隔离。该病例于2/22观看过Brigham Young University 篮球赛。
case.comments_en: The first case in Utah, a patient is older than 60 and is a resident of Davis County. Officials want to protect the person's identity and are not releasing further details. The patient attended a basketball game at Brigham Young University on Feb. 22

case.comments: 北加Alameda County确诊第二例，该患者为一名老人，曾搭乘至尊公主号，有其他病史。
case.comments_en: A new case of the novel coronavirus from a passenger who was on the now-quarantined Grand Princess cruise ship has been confirmed in Northern California’s Alameda County. The patient is an older adult who has underlying health conditions and is currently hospitalized.

case.comments: 一名在旧金山办公的FBI工作人员被确诊。
case.comments_en: An FBI agent who works in a satellite office in San Francisco has been diagnosed with COVID-19, the agency announced Friday night.

case.comments: 3月6日早上新增11例中的2例，坐标Rockland County， 都在以色列青年的成人礼上工作。
case.comments_en: 11 new cases that brought the total to 33 involved: 2 people in Rockland County who worked at a bat mitzvah at Young Israel.

case.comments: 3月6日早上新增11例中的1例，坐标New York City。
case.comments_en: 11 new cases that brought the total to 33 involved: 1 in New York City.

case.comments: 曾乘坐至尊公主号的六名退伍军人中的一名在Ventura County确诊
case.comments_en: A positive COVID-19 patient was tested in Ventura County, one of six Venturans who had been passengers aboard the Grand Princess.

case.comments: 据当地官方3/6统计，Solano County目前有3人感染。
case.comments_en: At this time, there are three confirmed cases of Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19) in Solano County.

case.comments: 本周Sonoma County有两名确诊患者，曾搭乘至尊公主号。
case.comments_en: This week the Sonoma County Department of Health Services (DHS) confirmed 2 presumptive positive case of novel coronavirus in Sonoma County residents with recent international travel on the Grand Princess (Princess Cruises) to Mexico.

case.comments: 该患者近期曾前往意大利。
case.comments_en: The individual from Cobb was diagnosed following a recent trip to Italy and is isolated at home, authorities said.

case.comments: 该患者正在住院治疗。
case.comments_en: The source of the Fulton County case has not been identified.

case.comments: 一位非佛州居民在Lee County测试阳性。该患者正在接受隔离治疗。
case.comments_en: The department of health also confirmed that there is one other presumptive case in Lee County. According to officials, the individual is isolated and being cared for.

case.comments: Pinal County新增2例确诊病例。至此，AZ一共确诊5例。新增患者年龄性别不详，但是来自同一个家庭。有报道称，这可能是Pinal County社区传播导致的。
links: New case of coronavirus in Arizona believed to be 'community spread'
case.comments_en: Two more people have now tested positive for the coronavirus in Arizona. Five cases of coronavirus now reported in Arizona

case.comments_en: Elected officials in Queens announced on Saturday morning that there is a novel coronavirus case in Rockaway. The person who contracted the virus is an Uber driver, according to NY1.

case.comments: 纽约新增至76例确诊！其中新增7例来自NYC。【更新】三名来自布鲁克林：两名60多岁女性去过埃及，已经一名30多岁男性去过意大利，目前状况危机。
case.comments_en: New York was up to 76 cases as of Saturday afternoon, the vast majority of which were in Westchester County and tied to a lawyer who works in midtown Manhattan

case.comments: 纽约3/7日中午宣布一共有76例确诊，其中2例来自Saratoga County。
case.comments_en: There are two confirmed cases in the Saratoga County, Cuomo said. The people involved are 57 and 52 years old.

case.comments: Clark County第一例，70多岁男性。已经隔离。
case.comments_en: The confirmed case is a male in his 70s. He has been in isolation, pending test results, and remains in isolation.

case.comments: 纽约3/7日中午宣布确诊人数增至76，其中23例来自Westchester。
case.comments_en: New York was up to 76 cases as of Saturday afternoon, 23 new cases bringing Westchester County’s infected population to 57 people — the most in New York state.

case.comments: 俄勒冈州新增4例中的其中2例，杰克逊县的病例是来自一个家庭的两个成年人，年龄在55至74岁之间。与旅行有关，尚未住院。
case.comments_en: The Jackson County cases are two adults from one household who are between the ages of 55 and 74, according to Dr. Jim Shames, the county’s public health officer. The cases are travel-related and the two adults have not been hospitalized, he said.

case.comments: 俄勒冈州新增4例其中的1例，克拉马斯县的病例没有详细信息，官方透露这例也与旅行有关。
case.comments_en: The Klamath county case also is travel-related.

case.comments: 马萨诸塞州新增5例，至此麻州总人确诊人数达13例。五名患者中有四人来Middlesex County，其中一名40多岁的女性、一名50多岁的女性、一名40多岁的男性和一名60多岁的男性。在最新的5个病例中，有3个患者“与Biogen员工会议有直接联系”。另一名患者最近前往意大利北部。
case.comments_en: Five new cases of coronavirus reported, bringing Mass. total to 13.Four of the five patients are from Middlesex County. Mass. DPH says the Middlesex County cases involve a woman in her 40s, a woman in her 50s, a man in his 40s and a man in his 60s.

case.comments: 俄勒冈州新增4例其中的1例，华盛顿县的病例是由于与那里的一个已知病例接触造成的。该人不需要医疗。
case.comments_en: The Washington County case resulted from contact with a known case there, health officials said. The person did not need medical attention.

case.comments: CA新增1例，同时也是Medera county 的首例确诊。患者近期去过至尊公主号游轮，具体信息不详。
case.comments_en: Madera County reports 1st confirmed coronavirus case in Central Valley, who returned from the Grand Princess cruise.

case.comments: 华盛顿州官网3/7更新，King County已经更至71例确诊。死亡人数新增4人。【更新】男，70多岁；女，70多岁；女，80多岁；女，80多岁。
case.comments_en: The confirmed number in King County has been updated to 71 right now, according to coronavirus page on the official site of WA, along with 4 more deaths reported. [UPDATE] deaths are male in his 70s, female in her 70s, female in her 80s, and female in her 80s.

case.comments: 华盛顿州官网再次更新Snohomish地区数据，新增8名患者。其中5人与LifeCare Center相关，包括4名女性(年龄为30多，40多，50多，60多岁各一名)，和一名男性(40多岁)。其他两名男性(40多岁和60多岁)和一名女性(80多岁)感染原因不明。
case.comments_en: 8 more cases were reported on the Coronavirus page of WA official website. 5 cases are connected to LifeCare Center, and 3 are still under investigation.

case.comments: 佛罗里达州官方宣布一名位于Charlotte County的新确诊患者。患者目前居家隔离，并被妥善照料。
case.comments_en: Florida Department of Health has announced a new presumptive positive Florida COVID-19 case in Charlotte County: the individual is isolated and being appropriately cared for.

case.comments: 斯坦福一名教职人员确诊。校方称，该教职人员出现症状后没有出现在工作环境。
case.comments_en: Stanford University faculty member tests positive for COVID-19: A Stanford University faculty member who has “ not been in the work environment since experiencing symptoms” tested positive for the new coronavirus, according to university officials.

case.comments: 一名Santa Cruz居民确诊，为本地第一例确诊病例，近期曾乘坐至尊公主号游轮。
case.comments_en: A Santa Cruz County resident who recently traveled on the Grand Princess cruise ship is the county's first confirmed case of COVID-19, officials said Saturday.

case.comments: Gilroy首例确诊病例，为五十多岁男性，起初被诊断为普通肺炎，后转移到San Jose的Kaiser Permanente，测出新冠阳性。
case.comments_en: A Gilroy resident has tested positive for COVID-19, marking the first known case of the virus in the city. The male resident, who has been identified as being in his 50s, was initially thought to have pneumonia, but was transferred to Kaiser Permanente in San Jose where he tested positive for COVID-19.

case.comments: 旧金山新增6例，三男三女，其中两名20多岁患者，3名40多岁患者以及一名50多岁患者。其中一位FBI工作人员在3/6已经报道。
case.comments_en: Of the six new patients, three are women and three are men. Two patients are in their 20s, three in their 40s, and one in their 50s, officials said. One of them is an FBI agent reported previously.

case.comments: LA新增1例，该患者近期在DC参加AIPAC会议，曾与一名已确诊患者有接触。
case.comments_en: LA County health officials have confirmed a new case of COVID-19 in Los Angeles County. The additional positive case is a resident who recently returned from attending the AIPAC Conference in Washington, D.C. where there was a known exposure to a person who was positive for COVID-19.

case.comments: Kittitas County第一例确诊，为一名67岁的女性，目前在家隔离
case.comments_en: Kittitas County on Saturday announced that a 67-year-old woman tested positive for COVID-19. She is currently in home isolation with her spouse, public health officials said.

case.comments: MA新增5例中的一例，坐标Berkshire，一名60多岁男性。
case.comments_en: The fifth patient is a man in his 60s from Berkshire County.

case.comments: DC特区感染第一人。该患者系50多岁的男性，是Christ Church Georgetown教区的教区长，在上周参加过三次礼拜，出席者550余人。
case.comments_en: The first confirmed case of coronavirus in the District is the rector of Christ Church Georgetown. He is in his 50s and was present for three services last week attended by 550 people.

case.comments: Santa Clara今日共新增8个案例，包括之前更新的斯坦福确诊患者（#412）和Gilroy的确诊患者（#413）。官方未披露更多信息。
case.comments_en: 8 new cases confirmed in Santa Clara, including two previously updated cases (NO 412, NO 413). Due to medical privacy requirements and to protect their identity, further information about these cases will not be released.

case.comments: 宾州Montgomery County确认两例病患。两人曾到访过美国其他有病患的地方，目前均在家隔离，症状轻微。
case.comments_en: Two cases of coronavirus were confirmed in Montgomery County. The individuals “have mild symptoms, are in isolation at home and were exposed to an area of the United States where covid-19 is present.” Details on where the patients lives were not immediately available.

case.comments: 纽约新增13例，全部来自Westchester。
case.comments_en: 13 new cases in New York, United States. All of the new cases are in Westchester County

case.comments: 堪萨斯州首例确诊，一名不到50岁的女性。【更新】该患者目前在University of Kansas Hospital就诊。
case.comments_en: First case in Kansas, a Kansas woman has tested positive for the novel coronavirus, the woman is under 50 years old and lives in Johnson County. The woman is in home isolation. [Update] The patient is admitted to the.

case.comments: 佛罗里达州新增2例中的另1例，坐标Volusia，有过旅行经历。

[Update] Family Of St. Louis County Woman With Coronavirus Violated Quarantine By Going To School Dance. St. Louis County Executive Sam Page expressed frustration during a Sunday evening press conference, where he announced that the St. Louis County Public Health department may institute a formal quarantine that would legally require the family to remain in their home.

case.comments: 纽约3/7日中午宣布一共有76例确诊，其中2位是一名在Upper West Side的男性的家庭成员。
case.comments_en: Two of 12 NYC cases by 3/7 include two family members of an Upper West Side man who tested positive.

case.comments: 该患者近期从意大利返回，目前在家隔离。

case.comments: 印第安纳州第二例患者， 该患者为 Hendricks County居民，目前只有轻微症状，现在家自我隔离。该患者在2月 末参加了biogen 的公司年会，于3月2号开始有流感样症状。现在全国范围内有差不多10多名患者的发病与这次会议有关，其中也包括了印第安纳州第一例患者，这位Marion County的患者现在仍然只有轻微症状，现在家隔离。
case.comments_en:
The patient lives in Hendricks County and tested 'presumptive positive'. The patient is in isolation with mild symptoms and is not hospitalized, according to ISDH.

"The patient traveled to Boston in late February to attend the BioGen conference and developed mild flu-like symptoms on March 2," ISDH said in a press release issued Sunday. More than a dozen COVID-19 cases nationwide have been tied to that conference, including the patient in Marion County who was identified Friday as the state's first coronavirus case. The Marion County patient also remains in isolation at this time with mild symptoms.

The latest case is a resident of Carver County who's in their 50s, and likely was exposed to the virus while traveling in Europe in late February. The patient developed symptoms on March 2 and sought medical treatment on Saturday; testing came back positive Sunday. The person is in isolation at home and is recovering.

The patient is a man in his 50s who is recovering in isolation at home. case.comments: 夏威夷第二例确诊，一名Oahu岛老人，近期曾到华盛顿州旅行。他在3月2日发病，4日回到夏威夷并直接去了医院，但在初次就诊时未进行COVID-19测试。 7日被一辆救护车送往医院，随后确诊。
case.comments_en: Department of Health officials announced a second case of COVID-19 in Hawaii on Sunday. He is an elderly man who lives on Oahu who recently traveled to Washington State. Officials said he fell ill on March 2 and returned to Hawaii on March 4 when he went directly to a hospital. During his initial visit, a coronavirus test was not done. An ambulance then took him to a hospital on March 7 when hospital staff then decided to conduct the COVID-19 test, which came back as a presumptive positive.

One individual is from Fulton County, an employee at Fulton County School. Fulton County Schools has decided to enact immediate dismissal at the impacted schools."

One individual is a Waffle House employee from Cherokee County. The employee has not been at work since March 1 and has been released from the hospital under quarantine, the company said in a statement. “We temporarily have closed the restaurant located at 1849 Marietta Hwy in Canton, GA.,” the statement said. “During the restaurant closure, we sanitized the restaurant thoroughly, using methods specifically designed to clean and disinfect.”

case.comments:

case.comments_en:
Officials also announced four new presumed cases of coronavirus Tuesday, bringing the state total to 15 just a day after Gov. Phil Murphy declared a public health emergency to set efforts in motion to keep the virus from spreading. 
Two of the new cases were in Bergen County, including the patient who died. The county now has seven presumed coronavirus cases. Some of those patients have links to a cluster of cases in Westchester County, New York. 
{UPDATE] by 3/10/2020
A 69-year-old man in New Jersey was the first person in the state to die from the new coronavirus, officials announced on Tuesday.

The man, who lives in Bergen County, had a history of health problems before contracting coronavirus, the state’s health commissioner, Judith Persichilli, said.

He was admitted to Hackensack Medical Center over the weekend, and suffered two heart attacks, Ms. Persichilli said. Three other people tested positive on Tuesday for coronavirus in New Jersey, bringing the statewide total to 15.

case.comments_en: A fifth presumptive positive case of coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) has been reported to the Nebraska Department of Health and Human Services (DHHS). DHHS is awaiting final confirmation from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC). 【update】The Lincoln-Lancaster County Health Department (LLCHD) today confirmed that a student who attended the girls’ state high school basketball games in Lincoln last week has been diagnosed with COVID-19. Local health officials have contacted the Lincoln relatives with whom the student stayed and are investigating any other contacts the student may have had in the community. The Lincoln relatives are currently self-quarantined and display no symptoms. The student arrived in Lincoln March 4 and stayed with relatives. The student is reported to have gone onto the basketball court after the 9 a.m. game to hug family members.

case.comments_en:
Two more presumptive cases of COVID-19 have been confirmed through state testing in residents of Ramsey and Olmsted counties, public health officials said Wednesday morning. 
In both instances, the patients have international travel history, with both currently recovering from home.

The Olmsted County case, a patient in their 50s, showed symptoms on Mar. 5 and sought testing on Mar. 9. They became symptomatic at work.

The Olmsted case involved someone who may have been infectious while at work, and state health officials are working with that employer now to identify anyone who may now be at risk.

case.comments_en: Los Angeles County reported its first coronavirus-related death on Wednesday and announced six new cases, including one suspected of being community-acquired. The person who died was a woman over 60 who wasn’t a resident and was visiting friends, Los Angeles County Department of Public Health director Barbara Ferrer said at news conference Wednesday. The woman had recently traveled extensively over the past month, including having a long layover in South Korea.

case.comments: 洛杉矶新增确诊6例。新病例中，有一人感染源不明，疑似为洛杉矶第二起社区传染病例。
case.comments_en: Los Angeles County reported its first coronavirus-related death on Wednesday and announced six new cases, including one suspected of being community-acquired. Officials also reported six additional positive cases, bringing the total number of cases up to 27 in the county. This also includes the three cases previously reported by the city of Long Beach. Three of the new reported cases were people who were in contact with a previously identified coronavirus case in the county. Another case involves a person who had traveled to France and returned home sick. Another case involves someone who had traveled to a religious conference in another state and came in contact with an infected person. Ferrer said one of the new cases is believed to be L.A. County’s second case of suspected community-acquired infection. That person is hospitalized.

news.comments_en: Los Angeles County reported its first coronavirus-related death on Wednesday and announced six new cases, including one suspected of being community-acquired. Three of the new reported cases were people who were in contact with a previously identified coronavirus case in the county. Another case involves a person who had traveled to France and returned home sick. Another case involves someone who had traveled to a religious conference in another state and came in contact with an infected person. Ferrer said one of the new cases is believed to be L.A. County’s second case of suspected community-acquired infection. That person is hospitalized.

news.comments_en:
Earlier Tuesday, the county confirmed that a resident at a senior living facility tested positive for the new coronavirus and was hospitalized. An email sent Monday to family members of residents at the Carlton Senior Living Elk Grove — which has approximately 140 residents — stated a resident there tested positive.

It appears to be the first confirmed COVID-19 case in a California senior facility. County public health departments, however, have only released limited details about where individual cases are confirmed, so there could be more that have not been made public.
Sacramento County announces a resident in their 90s has died of complications from coronavirus. The person was in an assisted living facility with an underlying health condition. The death is the third coronavirus-related death in the state.On Tuesday, Sacramento County health officials announced that a patient in her 90s at an Elk Grove nursing home had died from COVID-19. The woman is the third confirmed death from COVID-19 in California, and she is the state’s first known case of infection with the coronavirus in a nursing home. Health officials said that all patients in the nursing home would be tested for the virus, but that effort was delayed by a lack of test kits.

news.comments_en:
Officials also announced four new presumed cases of coronavirus Tuesday, bringing the state total to 15 just a day after Gov. Phil Murphy declared a public health emergency to set efforts in motion to keep the virus from spreading. 
Two of the new cases were in Bergen County, including the patient who died. The county now has seven presumed coronavirus cases. Some of those patients have links to a cluster of cases in Westchester County, New York. 
{UPDATE] by 3/10/2020
A 69-year-old man in New Jersey was the first person in the state to die from the new coronavirus, officials announced on Tuesday.

The man, who lives in Bergen County, had a history of health problems before contracting coronavirus, the state’s health commissioner, Judith Persichilli, said.

He was admitted to Hackensack Medical Center over the weekend, and suffered two heart attacks, Ms. Persichilli said. Three other people tested positive on Tuesday for coronavirus in New Jersey, bringing the statewide total to 15.

There are now nine cases of coronavirus in San Mateo County, public health officials said Monday.

The individual is a resident of Arlington County in their 60s who developed fever, cough and shortness of breath after having returned from international travel.  The resident is receiving medical care and is currently recuperating.  The positive result returned Sunday evening is considered presumptive, pending confirmation by the CDC.

news.comments: 周日晚上Parkview Noble医院的一名患者确诊，是印第安纳州东北部首例确诊患者，目前在医院隔离。
news.comments_en: An individual at Parkview Noble Hospital has been diagnosed with COVID-19 -- the first time someone in northeast Indiana has been identified as a coronavirus patient. The patient was tested after showing symptoms consistent with the illness. The swab was taken at Parkview Noble Hospital, where he is now in isolation. The superintendent there said that the district was aware of the matter and that the individual who was diagnosed "does not have any school age children and does not live in Kendallville or our district."

news.comments: 乔治亚周日新增4例病例，其中一位坐标Cherokee County。目前住院中。【更新】患者为Waffle House的员工，3月1号以后没有上班，所在餐厅已关门，在进行彻底消毒。
news.comments_en: The Georgia Department of Public Health announce addition of four presumptive positive cases of COVID-19 on Sunday night. One individual is a Waffle House employee from Cherokee County. The employee has not been at work since March 1 and has been released from the hospital under quarantine, the company said in a statement. “We temporarily have closed the restaurant located at 1849 Marietta Hwy in Canton, GA.,” the statement said. “During the restaurant closure, we sanitized the restaurant thoroughly, using methods specifically designed to clean and disinfect.”

news.comments: 乔治亚周日新增4例病例，其中一位坐标Fulton County。目前住院中。【更新】其中一名病例为Fulton County School的员工，Fulton County School宣布所有受影响学校停课。
news.comments_en: The Georgia Department of Public Health announce addition of four presumptive positive cases of COVID-19 on Sunday night. One individual is from Fulton County, an employee at Fulton County School. Fulton County Schools has decided to enact immediate dismissal at the impacted schools."

news.comments: 夏威夷第二例确诊，一名Oahu岛老人，近期曾到华盛顿州旅行。他在3月2日发病，4日回到夏威夷并直接去了医院，但在初次就诊时未进行COVID-19测试。 7日被一辆救护车送往医院，随后确诊。
news.comments_en: Department of Health officials announced a second case of COVID-19 in Hawaii on Sunday. He is an elderly man who lives on Oahu who recently traveled to Washington State. Officials said he fell ill on March 2 and returned to Hawaii on March 4 when he went directly to a hospital. During his initial visit, a coronavirus test was not done. An ambulance then took him to a hospital on March 7 when hospital staff then decided to conduct the COVID-19 test, which came back as a presumptive positive.

news.comments_en: Shasta County, California, has confirmed its first presumptive positive case of coronavirus, the county’s health and human services agency announced in a press release Sunday. The patient is a man in his 50s who is recovering in isolation at home. He had a history of recent travel and public health staff are working to identify anyone who may have been in close contact with the patient, the release said.

The latest case is a resident of Carver County who's in their 50s, and likely was exposed to the virus while traveling in Europe in late February. The patient developed symptoms on March 2 and sought medical treatment on Saturday; testing came back positive Sunday. The person is in isolation at home and is recovering.

Two of the individuals had underlying health conditions while one did not. None required hospitalization and are recovering at home in isolation. All three individuals were part of a cruise in Egypt.

news.comments: 印第安纳州第二例患者， 该患者为 Hendricks County居民，目前只有轻微症状，现在家自我隔离。该患者在2月 末参加了biogen 的公司年会，于3月2号开始有流感样症状。现在全国范围内有差不多10多名患者的发病与这次会议有关，其中也包括了印第安纳州第一例患者，这位Marion County的患者现在仍然只有轻微症状，现在家隔离。
news.comments_en:
The patient lives in Hendricks County and tested 'presumptive positive'. The patient is in isolation with mild symptoms and is not hospitalized, according to ISDH.

"The patient traveled to Boston in late February to attend the BioGen conference and developed mild flu-like symptoms on March 2," ISDH said in a press release issued Sunday. More than a dozen COVID-19 cases nationwide have been tied to that conference, including the patient in Marion County who was identified Friday as the state's first coronavirus case. The Marion County patient also remains in isolation at this time with mild symptoms.

news.comments: 田纳西州第三例。患者系成年女性，已经自我隔离。并非旅行相关，原因待查。

City and state health officials are identifying other people she may have had contact with and still attempting to determine the origins of her infection.

news.comments: 首例康州本地居民感染(之前两例在康州工作，但是住在纽约州)。患者40多岁男性，目前在Danbury医院接受治疗。近期曾前往加州，与前两例康州确诊没有关系。
news.comments_en: This is the first Connecticut resident, a Wilton man, to test positive for COVID-19, which still needs to be confirmed by the CDC. (Previously reported two cases are not CT residents but work in CT.) The patient, a Wilton resident, who is between the ages of 40 and 50, is being treated at Danbury Hospital. The person most likely became infected with the virus that causes COVID-19 during a recent trip to California and sought medical care shortly after returning to Connecticut, Lamont said.

The person is said to be undergoing treatment at Eisenhower Health in Rancho Mirage. Public Health was following up on people who might have been exposed and an investigation was underway to determine how the individual contracted the disease.

news.comments: 3/7，官宣了两位死亡病例，这是其中的一例，患者生前在Life Care Center居住。另外一例我们已经在早些时候报道过了，同样还是EvergreenHealth医院的患者。
news.comments_en:
Two more deaths from coronavirus were reported Saturday, bringing the total to 17 in Washington state. So far, at least 104 have tested positive for COVID-19, health officials said.

One death is associated with Life Care Center while another is with a patient who was treated at EvergreenHealth Medical Hospital. The new death comes just one day after three people died at EvergreenHealth.

[Update] Family Of St. Louis County Woman With Coronavirus Violated Quarantine By Going To School Dance. St. Louis County Executive Sam Page expressed frustration during a Sunday evening press conference, where he announced that the St. Louis County Public Health department may institute a formal quarantine that would legally require the family to remain in their home.

news.comments: 40来岁男性，近期去过加州。
news.comments_en: A man in his 40s who recently traveled to California

news.comments_en: 3 of the new cases are in Nassau County

news.comments: 纽约3月6日下午新增11例中在Westchester的8例。

news.comments_en: 21 out of 46 people tested positive for #coronavirus on the cruise ship in San Francisco 2 passengers and 19 crew member.

news.comments_en: The first Nebraskan to test positive for the coronavirus is a 36-year-old Omaha woman. It is currently unknown whether the patient's immediate family members have been exposed. An investigation is underway by an epidemiology team to see who else this individual has had contact with and where.

news.comments: 两位丹佛市居民被确诊。均表现出症状，但尚未住院。两位患者最近都有州外的旅游史， 一位患者刚从加拿大温哥华回来，另一位患者坐了邮轮回来，但是官方没有给出邮轮的具体信息。这两位患者是科罗拉多州的第4，5位患者。
news.comments_en:
Denver health officials on Friday said two city residents have tested positive for the novel coronavirus.
both patients recently returned from out-of-state travel — one from Vancouver, Canada, and one from a cruise ship, though officials did not say where the cruise had gone.

news.comments: 肯塔基州确认首例。患者在Lexington，已经隔离。目前没有更详细的信息。
news.comments_en: Gov. Beshear confirmed the case was in Lexington, and the person is isolated. Beshear declared a state of emergency, but said the threat to the general population is low.

news.comments: 明州Ramsay郡的一名老年女性被确认为明州首例。该患者之前曾乘坐游轮，2月25日出现症状，3月3日就诊。现在在家中隔离恢复。
news.comments_en: A Ramsey County woman is the first to have a presumptive case of the new COVID-19 coronavirus in Minnesota. The case is an older woman who recently travelled on a cruise ship and is now recovering at home.The patient began to develop symptoms on Feb. 25 and sought health care on Mar. 3.

news.comments: 最新消息称Snohomish County已有共19例确诊患者
news.comments_en: As of the 11 a.m. Department of Health Update, there were 58 cases in King County, 19 cases in Snohomish County, one case in Grant County and one case in Jefferson County, which includes Port Townsend on the Olympic Peninsula.

news.comments_en: As of the 11 a.m. Department of Health Update, there were 58 cases in King County, 19 cases in Snohomish County, one case in Grant County and one case in Jefferson County, which includes Port Townsend on the Olympic Peninsula.

news.comments: 三位患者都在2月11至21日搭乘了至尊公主号游轮前往墨西哥。目前三人症状轻微，在家隔离。
news.comments_en: The three new cases were from South and Mid Placer and all traveled on the Grand Princess cruise ship from San Francisco to Mexico Feb. 11-21. Two had mild symptoms that have already resolved; the third currently has mild symptoms. All three are isolated at home and none required hospitalization.

news.comments_en: One case in Jefferson County confirmed; University of Washington announced that starting on Monday classes will no longer be meeting in person through the end of winter quarter.

news.comments: 患者是一位60余岁的男性，目前正在住院治疗。患者的样本在新泽西州卫生局检测出阳性，现已被送往CDC进行最终确认。

news.comments_en: 3 new coronavirus patients confirmed in Contra Costa County. The three new patients are in isolation in their homes, according to officials. Two of the patients were passengers aboard the Grand Princess cruise ship. Another one is known to have had close contact with a coronavirus patient in another jurisdiction.

news.comments_en: 3 new coronavirus patients confirmed in Contra Costa County. The three new patients are in isolation in their homes, according to officials. She’s now quarantined at home.

The diagnosed employee lives in orange County and is under a self-quarantine; she also did not have direct contact with customers.

news.comments_en: a Grant County resident, in isolation at Central Washington Hospital in Wenatchee. First admitted to the hospital Saturday, but at the time the person did not meet the state’s requirements for testing. After the state loosened testing requirements on travel history Monday, the patient met the criteria for testing, and confirmed positive on Wednesday. Between Saturday and Monday, the patient was in the hospital but not under isolation. [Update] The patient has died on 3/8.

news.comments_en: Two evacuees from the Diamond Princess who were quarantined at Joint Base San Antonio-Lackland are infected with coronavirus.

news.comments: 加州首府Sacramento确诊该郡第一例患者。患者返美旅途中就采取了防范措施，回到加州后自我隔离，目前情况良好，在家继续隔离。
news.comments_en: 1st case of coronavirus in Sacramento County. Doing quite well.

news.comments: 美国第17例，患者在加州一个偏远的地方。目前健康状况良好，在家隔离。官方没有透露其他任何消息。
news.comments_en: First case of COVID-19 confirmed in Humboldt County. Doing well and self-isolating at home

news.comments: 日本游轮钻石公主号撤侨返回人员。目前在Napa。这是湾区第五例。
news.comments_en: First case in Napa County. Among the dozens of Americans on the Princess Diamond cruise ship under quarantine in Japan.

news.comments: 美国第十五例确诊：2月7日从武汉返美的撤侨人员，性别男。一直在圣安东尼奥一处美军基地。同行91人都在被继续隔离。
news.comments_en: The individual was part of a group that arrived at San Antonio Air Force base on a State Department-chartered flight from Wuhan. Of the 91 people on the flight, only one showed symptoms.

news.comments: 美国确诊第十四例，也是之前撤侨飞机上回来的，2月7日入境之后在圣地亚哥一个美军基地被隔离。
news.comments_en: The patient returned to the U.S. on a State Department-chartered flight. Under a federal quarantine order after arrival on Feb 7, 2020.

news.comments: 患者之前随撤侨飞机从武汉返美，在圣地亚哥一个美军基地入境。美国CDC对随机返回者进行隔离两周。患者目前状况良好，正在被继续隔离。评论：两次撤侨目前仅发现一人确诊，比例之低，美国真是开挂！
news.comments_en: The patient had been evacuated from Wuhan and under a 14-day quarantine at Marine Corps Air Station Miramar. Minimal symptoms. The patient had initially been released  back to quarantine after a possible mix-up with the test results.

news.comments: 美国第十二例，威斯康星第一例确诊。所在地是madison，威斯康星大学主校区。患者过去两周去过中国，在国内接触过的人里有人确诊。这位患者目前情况良好，不需要住院，已经回家隔离。威斯康星还有十人在被检测，七人已经被排除(test negative)。出于隐私保护，患者所有信息保密。
news.comments_en: The patient is a Wisconsin resident who recently visited Beijing, China. the patient is doing well and is no longer in the hospital.

news.comments: 除两次出门看病，没有离开家。
news.comments_en: A female who traveled from China to visit family in Santa Clara County is the second Bay Area case.Since arriving on January 23, she has only left her family's home twice to seek outpatient medical care

news.comments: 没去过武汉，被丈夫传染。【update】夫妻病情恶化后，被转移到UCSF治疗，但患者于3/4号痊愈。
news.comments_en:
Person to person transmission, by her husband.

Both San Benito County coronavirus patients recovered

news.comments: 这对夫妇，丈夫从中国返回，就没离开家。【update】夫妻病情恶化后，被转移到UCSF治疗，但患者于3/4号痊愈。
news.comments_en:
The San Benito County cases are a husband and wife, both 57. The husband recently traveled to Wuhan, but his wife did not travel with him.

Both San Benito County coronavirus patients recovered

news.comments: Umass Boston学生，二十多岁。
news.comments_en: UMass Boston student, young man in 20s

news.comments: 除两次出门看病外，没有离开家。
news.comments_en: First Bay Area Case. He recently traveled to Wuhan. He has largely been isolated at home since he returned to San Jose International Airport on Jan. 24 and only left his home twice to seek outpatient medical care.

news.comments: 美国第二例、芝加哥第一例确诊者的丈夫。没有去过疫区，是美国首例人传人。他在PIRHL LLC工作，曾去俄亥俄cleveland办公室出差。其孙子已经有发烧症状【已排除】
news.comments_en: First person-to-person transmission case. Husband of Chicago's first confirmed case. Works for PIRHL LLC. Recently visited the company's Cleveland office.

news.comments: 患者到达洛杉矶机场之后，从机场立刻被送往医院。
news.comments_en: The patient arrived in Los Angeles Airport and was immediately sent to hospital.

news.comments: 亚利桑那州立大学学生。去过疫情爆发地 - 华南海鲜市场。并未住校内宿舍，而是在Tempe租房。
news.comments_en: ASU student who visited Wuhan recently. He lives in Tempe, not on campus.

news.comments: 这位患者的信息很少。入境机场和入境时间均无报道提及。
news.comments_en: A man in his fifties who arrived from Wuhan at LAX — is currently in isolation in a local hospital and in good condition.

news.comments: 丈夫没有去过武汉，被间接感染，成为美国Person to person传染的第一例。
news.comments_en: A Chicago woman in her 60s returned to the United States on Jan. 13 from Wuhan, China. She's in stable condition and doing well.

news.comments: 美国第一例新肺炎患者，机器人配备摄像头、麦克风和听诊器，主治医生隔着玻璃窗户，操作医疗机器人进行治疗。患者住院前6天没有好转，第七天服用了一种治疗埃博拉病毒的实验性药物Remdesivir。之后迅速治愈，目前已经出院。
news.comments_en: The man, in his 30s, was the first confirmed case of US. He was evaluated using a robot. Fully recovered by now.
